The paper presents a randomized algorithm for the k-server problem on hierarchically separated trees (HSTs) using online mirror descent with a multiscale entropy mirror map. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.IT (information theory), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.GT (computational geometry), and cs.SI (social and information networks). However, given that the paper focuses on algorithm design and analysis, cs.DS is the most likely category. The use of entropy and regularization techniques also suggests a potential fit with cs.IT and cs.LG. The mention of HST embeddings and metric spaces further supports the possibility of cs.GT and cs.SI.
